Cadel Evans Wins Tour de France, Australia’s First; Cavendish Takes Stage

-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 
2011-07-24T15:29:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-24/cadel-evans-wins-tour-de-france-australia-s-first-cavendish-takes-stage.html
Cadel Evans  won the  Tour de France ,
becoming the first Australian to clinch road cycling’s premier
event, as the three-week race finished today in Paris.   Evans, 34, runner-up in 2007 and 2008, finishes ahead of
Luxembourg’s  Andy Schleck  in the overall standings. He took the
race leader’s yellow jersey from Schleck following yesterday’s
individual time trial.   Mark Cavendish  won the final sprint on today’s stage, which
ended on the Champs-Elysees in Paris.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  